menu "Ring Buffer"

config RING_BUFFER
    bool "Enable ring buffer support"
    default y
    help
      Enables the SPSC (single-producer / single-consumer) lock-free ring
      buffer (vibe_rb_t). Used by the UART driver and the shell subsystem.
      Disable to exclude the ring buffer entirely and save flash.

config RING_BUFFER_STATS
    bool "Enable ring buffer statistics"
    default n
    depends on RING_BUFFER
    help
      Adds per-instance statistics counters to every vibe_rb_t:
        peak_used   — peak occupancy ever observed (bytes)
        put_count   — total bytes successfully written
        get_count   — total bytes successfully read
        drop_count  — bytes dropped because the buffer was full

      Retrieve with vibe_rb_get_stats(rb, &s).
      Reset with vibe_rb_reset_stats(rb).

      Cost: 4 × size_t (~16 bytes) per ring buffer instance plus a few
      counter increments on every put/get call.

endmenu
